<br>
This will be my last post on this thread.<br>
<br>
I have reread all of the posts thus far written, and I've got to say, 85% of them are covering stuff that has already been covered and solved.<br>
<br>
1.)  Pyro will announce his intentions on dragon kills.<br>
<br>
2.)  FoV will join the rotation.<br>
<br>
3.)  FoV members are Far from UBER, seeing as most people of the same lvl have as good or better gear by far.  I don't have ONE peice of no drop or planar armor, only what i've looted or saved and bought myself, as anyone could do with a normal lvl 45-50 char.<br>
<br>
4.) Everyone got thier panties on a bunch after misreading quotes an taking things out of context on most of what they read.  If you plan on quoting someone, at least make sure it is something THAT PERSON wrote.  I've seen it said Many times now that Pyro stated he wants to &quot;Monopolize&quot; the dragons and KS anyone that gets in his way.  Umm....he only said he wants to kill them when no one else is....as in....they are FFA...and no one has on rotation.  It is stated in the rules themselves, if a dragon is on FFA and is killed before a guildleader knows that another guild has claimed...ie...on the same day a guild posts its own intentions...the Guild with the intentions of killing will be moved to the next spot on rotation and given the next turn, it's a 3 day delay on either dragon we've killed before a patch or crash.  3 Days, not a year of Monopoly.<br>
<br>
5.)  We (FoV) are NOT Lewt Whores that care about no one except our &quot;L33T Group of Mercenaries.&quot;  We GIVE AWAY epic peices to players Not in our guild, only because they needed them.<br>
<br>
6.) This thread is old, and the argument is pointless.  The only people still posting are ones posting the same questoins that were posted on the first page and answered on the first or second page of posts.  Or those that just want to stick their noses in on a debate that they have no reason to be in...ie....people with Not One character that can or might attend one of the aforementioned raids.  I agree with whoever it was that posted &quot;if you don't have anything more intelligent to add to this board, let it die&quot; not an exact quote, but close enough.<br>
<br>
I'm done here, if you want to discuss this further with me, contact me in game, i'll be lvling up somewhere enjoying the game i pay to play and the company of the friends i choose to keep.<br>
<br>
just my 2cp worth....<br>
<br>
Reptylle, Monk of 49 Scales<br>
